{"parentUuid":"0b5f969f-19fe-47c8-9e04-0cc9fdf08eca","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator","sessionId":"a4e11369-bc15-4ff1-9b18-115fc4dd0659","version":"2.1.41","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"buzzing-wobbling-rossum","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tooluse_U26VaulPbCKIH6CBIZfr1O","type":"tool_result","content":[{"text":"\n\nHere is the complete project summary.\n\n---\n\n## Project: CourtAssistant (法院助手)\n\n**Location:** `C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\CourtAssistant`\n\n**Project Type:** Native Android app written in Kotlin, using Jetpack Compose for UI.\n\n**Build System:** Gradle (Kotlin DSL), Android Gradle Plugin 8.2.2, Kotlin 1.9.22\n\n**Min SDK:** 26 (Android 8.0) | **Target SDK:** 34 (Android 14)\n\n---\n\n### What This App Does\n\nThis is a **Chinese court hearing assistant app** designed for lawyers/legal professionals. It automates the workflow of tracking court notifications received via SMS. The core pipeline is:\n\n1. **SMS Reading & Parsing** -- Reads all SMS messages from the phone, filters for court-related ones (keywords like \"法院\", \"开庭\", \"传票\", \"案号\"), and extracts structured data: case number, court name, hearing date/time, party names, and embedded URLs.\n\n2. **WebView for Document Service** -- Opens court document delivery URLs (送达链接) in an embedded WebView. When the user navigates to a PDF download link, the app intercepts it and downloads the PDF automatically.\n\n3. **PDF Download & Parsing** -- Downloads court documents (especially subpoenas/传票) and parses them using two strategies:\n   - **iText 7** for text-based PDFs\n   - **Google ML Kit Chinese OCR** as a fallback for scanned/image PDFs\n   Extracts 7 key fields: case number, court name, hearing time, defendant (被传唤人), judge/handler (承办人), location (应到处所), and phone number.\n\n4. **Calendar Sync** -- Automatically creates calendar events for court hearings with reminders at 1 day and 1 hour before. Deduplicates by case number + hearing time.\n\n5. **Local Database** -- Persists all SMS records and downloaded PDFs in a Room database with MD5-based deduplication for documents.\n\n---\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nCourtAssistant/\n├── build.gradle.kts                  # Root build config (AGP 8.2.2, Kotlin 1.9.22, KSP)\n├── settings.gradle.kts               # Project settings\n├── gradle.properties                 # JVM args (8GB heap), AndroidX enabled\n├── gradlew.bat                       # Gradle wrapper (Windows)\n├── local.properties                  # Local SDK path\n├── add-to-calendar.patch             # Empty patch file\n├── java_pid*.hprof                   # 3 heap dump files (~1.7GB total, likely debug artifacts)\n└── app/\n    ├── build.gradle.kts              # App module: Compose, Room, iText, ML Kit, OkHttp\n    ├── proguard-rules.pro\n    └── src/main/\n        ├── AndroidManifest.xml       # Permissions: SMS, Calendar, Internet\n        ├── res/                      # Drawables, strings, themes, file_paths.xml\n        └── java/com/court/assistant/\n            ├── CourtApp.kt           # Application class (lazy DB + Repository init)\n            ├── MainActivity.kt       # Entry point, permission handling, Compose setup\n            ├── calendar/\n            │   └── CalendarSync.kt   # Calendar event creation with dedup + reminders\n            ├── data/\n            │   ├── db/\n            │   │   ├── CourtDao.kt          # Room DAO (SMS + PDF CRUD)\n            │   │   ├── CourtDatabase.kt     # Room DB v2 with migration\n            │   │   ├── CourtSmsEntity.kt    # SMS table entity\n            │   │   └── PdfDocumentEntity.kt # PDF table entity (MD5 unique index)\n            │   └── repository/\n            │       └── CourtRepository.kt   # Repository layer\n            ├── pdf/\n            │   ├── PdfDownloadManager.kt    # OkHttp downloader with cookie support + MD5\n            │   └── PdfParser.kt             # iText + ML Kit OCR, extracts SubpoenaInfo\n            ├── sms/\n            │   ├── SmsParser.kt             # Regex-based SMS field extraction\n            │   └── SmsReader.kt             # ContentResolver SMS reader with keyword filter\n            ├── ui/\n            │   ├── MainScreen.kt            # SMS list with expandable cards\n            │   ├── Navigation.kt            # NavHost: main -> webview -> pdf preview\n            │   ├── PdfPreviewScreen.kt      # PDF renderer with hearing info card\n            │   ├── WebViewScreen.kt         # Embedded browser with auto PDF interception\n            │   └── theme/\n            │       ├── Theme.kt             # \"Song Dynasty aesthetic\" color scheme\n            │       └── Type.kt              # Serif typography\n            ├── utils/\n            │   └── Md5Util.kt               # File MD5 calculation\n            ├── viewmodel/\n            │   └── MainViewModel.kt         # Central ViewModel: SMS load, PDF download, calendar sync\n            └── webview/\n                └── CourtWebViewClient.kt    # Intercepts PDF URLs in WebView\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Dependencies\n\n| Library | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| Jetpack Compose + Material 3 | UI framework |\n| Room 2.6.1 | Local SQLite database |\n| iText 7.2.5 | PDF text extraction |\n| ML Kit Chinese OCR | Fallback OCR for scanned PDFs |\n| OkHttp 4.12 | PDF downloading |\n| Navigation Compose | Screen navigation |\n\n### Design Notes\n\n- The UI uses a custom \"Song Dynasty aesthetic\" (宋氏美学) theme with colors like Ivory, Cinnabar Red, Jade Green, and Amber Gold, with serif typography throughout.\n- The footer credits \"宋氏美学，单夫纯律师制作保留权利\" (Song aesthetic, rights reserved by lawyer Dan Fuchun).\n- The 3 `.hprof` heap dump files in the root are ~1.7GB combined and are debug artifacts that should likely be cleaned up.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acabb7d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 26051\ntool_uses: 29\nduration